TextBody:
Hi Glenda,

Thank you for reaching out to Netwrix support regarding your issue. I would be happy to assist you.

Thank you for taking the time to meet today.

Today we:

Performed an upgrade on the AIC to the latest available version (11.6.0.25) by performing the process mentioned in the documentation below:

Upgrade Procedure

Once the upgrade process was successfully completed we were able to view recent file system activity in the AIC on the desired hosts. 

Our next steps are:

You will:

Allow the File System 0.Collections job group to run through the scheduled tasks and verify that the information is displayed in the AIC if there are any new or updated file system activity or permission changes.

I will:

Continue to keep this ticket in an postponed reply status and I will reach out tomorrow for a status update on the AIC and FSAC system scan jobs. 

Thank you,

Scottie Taylor
Technical Support Engineer
____________________________
Cybersecurity That Works For You

6160 Warren Parkway, Suite 100, Frisco, TX 75034
www.netwrix.com

Hi Glenda,

Thank you for the updated information. Within the Netwrix Enterprise Auditor application, you have FSAA jobs that collect file system permissions and FSAC jobs that collect file system activity. In the ticket description, you mentioned that you were not able to view file data from the current file server. Is that type of data file system activity or permissions? If you're tracking file system activity, which would be different operations like read, write, added, delete etc. This would utilize the Activity Monitor agents and we would start troubleshooting this issue there. If it's permissions data that you're not seeing then verifying whether you're using proxies would be a great start there. 

Please let me know if you have any additional questions.

Thank you,

Scottie Taylor
Technical Support Engineer

1. Are you looking to run a report to identify a specific file and the time/date files from that server were deleted? If so, do you have a general idea of the range of time they were deleted? Yes
